query: Summarize the basic information of the sloops laid down by Denny, Dunbarton.
summary: Denny, Dunbarton laid down four Class Sloops: Chanticleer (U05), Crane (U23), Snipe (U20) and Sparrow (U71). Chanticleer was laid down on 6 June 1941 and launched on 24 September 1942. It was commissioned on 29 March 1943. Crane was laid down 13 June 1941 and launched 9 November 1942 before being commissioned 10 May 1943. Snipe was laid down 21 September 1944 and launched 20 December 1945 and finally commissioned on 9 September 1946. The last of the Sloops, Sparrow, was laid down 30 October 1944 and launched 18 February 1946 before being commissioned 16 December 1946.
